    arising from the sale, use, non-use, and/or distribution of such goods.
    Except as otherwise stated herein, merchandise that has been modified
    (in whatever form) may not be returned.

  p.md-title[style='padding-bottom: 10px;'] Defaults
  p.md-subhead All remaining balances owed to the Company shall be due on or
    before the estimated completion date of the order. The Customer shall not
    receive the order until the remaining balance is paid. If the Customer fails
    to make any payment on the due dates, without prejudice to any other right or
    remedy available to the Company, the Company shall be entitled to cancel the
    order or suspend further deliveries to the Customer.
  p.md-subhead All payments owed to Company shall be due on or within thirty
    (30) days from the date of an invoice.  Customer’s failure to make any
    payment as and when due to Company, to perform or observe any covenant or
    agreement contained herein, to comply with applicable law, or any condition
    shall occur that reasonably could be expected to lead to Customer’s
    insolvency, will create a default by Customer under these Terms and
    Conditions.
  p.md-subhead Except as provided herein, these Terms and Conditions incorporate
    by reference all terms of Article 2 of the Uniform Commercial Code,
    including but not limited to, all Company’s remedies.  On account of any
    delinquent payments or amounts, Customer agrees to pay an additional service
    charge equal to 1 ½% per month (18% per annum), collection agency fees equal
    to 30% of delinquent amounts, Company’s attorneys’ fees, and all other costs
    and expenses which may be incurred by the Company in furtherance of the
    collection of delinquent amounts and/or to enforce the terms and conditions
    set forth herein, or as otherwise provided by law.
  p.md-subhead[style='padding-bottom: 30px;'] Customer will pay Company a
    handling fee of $50 for any returned checks.  If Customer’s account is
    insured and Customer’s account is turned over to a receivable insurance
    company for a claim, Customer agrees to pay Company a charge equal to 30%
    of the principal amount due which is in default.

